snTrapChasPwrSupply.name: snTrapChasPwrSupply
snTrapChasPwrSupply.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a power supply fails to operate normally. The value is a packed bit string; the 2 power supplies status are encoded into 4 bits (a nibble). The following shows the meaning of each bit: (bit 0 is the least significant bit). bit position meaning ------------ ------- 4-31 reserved 3 Power Supply 2 DC (0=bad, 1=good). 2 Power Supply 1 DC (0=bad, 1=good). 1 Power Supply 2 present status (0=present, 1=not-present). 0 Power Supply 1 present status (0=present, 1=not-present).

snTrapLockedAddressViolation.name: snTrapLockedAddressViolation
snTrapLockedAddressViolation.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when more source MAC addresses are received from a port than the maximum number of addresses configured to that port.

snTrapOspfIfStateChange.name: snTrapOspfIfStateChange
snTrapOspfIfStateChange.description: An ospfIfStateChange trap signifies that there has been a change in the state of a non-virtual OSPF interface. This trap should be generated when the interface state regresses (e.g., goes from Dr to Down) or progresses to a terminal state (i.e., Point-to-Point, DR Other, Dr, or Backup).

snTrapOspfVirtIfStateChange.name: snTrapOspfVirtIfStateChange
snTrapOspfVirtIfStateChange.description: An ospfIfStateChange trap signifies that there has been a change in the state of an OSPF vir- tual interface. This trap should be generated when the inter- face state regresses (e.g., goes from Point- to-Point to Down) or progresses to a terminal state (i.e., Point-to-Point).

snOspfNbrStateChange.name: snOspfNbrStateChange
snOspfNbrStateChange.description: An ospfNbrStateChange trap signifies that there has been a change in the state of a non- virtual OSPF neighbor. This trap should be generated when the neighbor state regresses (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full to 1-Way or Down) or progresses to a terminal state (e.g., 2-Way or Full). When an neighbor transitions from or to Full on non-broadcast multi-access and broadcast networks, the trap should be gen- erated by the designated router. A designated router transitioning to Down will be noted by ospfIfStateChange.

snOspfVirtNbrStateChange.name: snOspfVirtNbrStateChange
snOspfVirtNbrStateChange.description: An ospfIfStateChange trap signifies that there has been a change in the state of an OSPF vir- tual neighbor. This trap should be generated when the neighbor state regresses (e.g., goes from Attempt or Full to 1-Way or Down) or progresses to a terminal state (e.g., Full).

snOspfIfConfigError.name: snOspfIfConfigError
snOspfIfConfigError.description: An ospfIfConfigError trap signifies that a packet has been received on a non-virtual in- terface from a router whose configuration parameters conflict with this router's confi- guration parameters. Note that the event op- tionMismatch should cause a trap only if it prevents an adjacency from forming.

snOspfVirtIfConfigError.name: snOspfVirtIfConfigError
snOspfVirtIfConfigError.description: An ospfConfigError trap signifies that a pack- et has been received on a virtual interface from a router whose configuration parameters conflict with this router's configuration parameters. Note that the event optionMismatch should cause a trap only if it prevents an ad- jacency from forming.

snOspfIfAuthFailure.name: snOspfIfAuthFailure
snOspfIfAuthFailure.description: An ospfIfAuthFailure trap signifies that a packet has been received on a non-virtual in- terface from a router whose authentication key or authentication type conflicts with this router's authentication key or authentication type.

snOspfVirtIfAuthFailure.name: snOspfVirtIfAuthFailure
snOspfVirtIfAuthFailure.description: An ospfVirtIfAuthFailure trap signifies that a packet has been received on a virtual interface from a router whose authentication key or au- thentication type conflicts with this router's authentication key or authentication type.

snOspfIfRxBadPacket.name: snOspfIfRxBadPacket
snOspfIfRxBadPacket.description: An ospfIfRxBadPacket trap signifies that an OSPF packet has been received on a non-virtual interface that cannot be parsed.

snOspfVirtIfRxBadPacket.name: snOspfVirtIfRxBadPacket
snOspfVirtIfRxBadPacket.description: An ospfRxBadPacket trap signifies that an OSPF packet has been received on a virtual interface that cannot be parsed.

snOspfTxRetransmit.name: snOspfTxRetransmit
snOspfTxRetransmit.description: An ospfTxRetransmit trap signifies than an OSPF packet has been retransmitted on a non- virtual interface. All packets that may be re- transmitted are associated with an LSDB entry. The LS type, LS ID, and Router ID are used to identify the LSDB entry.

ospfVirtIfTxRetransmit.name: ospfVirtIfTxRetransmit
ospfVirtIfTxRetransmit.description: An ospfTxRetransmit trap signifies than an OSPF packet has been retransmitted on a virtual interface. All packets that may be retransmit- ted are associated with an LSDB entry. The LS type, LS ID, and Router ID are used to identify the LSDB entry.

snOspfOriginateLsa.name: snOspfOriginateLsa
snOspfOriginateLsa.description: An ospfOriginateLsa trap signifies that a new LSA has been originated by this router. This trap should not be invoked for simple refreshes of LSAs (which happesn every 30 minutes), but instead will only be invoked when an LSA is (re)originated due to a topology change. Addi- tionally, this trap does not include LSAs that are being flushed because they have reached MaxAge.

snOspfMaxAgeLsa.name: snOspfMaxAgeLsa
snOspfMaxAgeLsa.description: An ospfMaxAgeLsa trap signifies that one of the LSA in the router's link-state database has aged to MaxAge.

snOspfLsdbOverflow.name: snOspfLsdbOverflow
snOspfLsdbOverflow.description: An ospfLsdbOverflow trap signifies that the number of LSAs in the router's link-state data- base has exceeded ospfExtLsdbLimit.

snOspfLsdbApproachingOverflow.name: snOspfLsdbApproachingOverflow
snOspfLsdbApproachingOverflow.description: An ospfLsdbApproachingOverflow trap signifies that the number of LSAs in the router's link- state database has exceeded ninety percent of ospfExtLsdbLimit.

snTrapOpticalMonitoringFoundryOpticsNotC.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if optical monitoring is enabled but the Foundry optic is not capable.

snTrapStaticMulticastMacConfigAdd.name: snTrapStaticMulticastMacConfigAdd
snTrapStaticMulticastMacConfigAdd.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if a new entry is added to static multicast mac configuration table. Format 1: Static Mac entry with Mac Address <xxxx:xxxx:xxxx> is added to portnumber <port> on VLAN <id> Format 2: Static Mac entry with Mac Address <xxxx:xxxx:xxxx> is added to portmask <0xXXXXXXXX-XXXXXXXX> on VLAN <id>

snTrapStaticMulticastMacConfigRemove.name: snTrapStaticMulticastMacConfigRemove
snTrapStaticMulticastMacConfigRemove.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if an entry is removed from static multicast mac configuration table . Format 1: Static Mac entry with Mac Address <xxxx:xxxx:xxxx> is deleted from portnumber <port> on VLAN <id> Format 2: Static Mac entry with Mac Address <xxxx:xxxx:xxxx> is deleted from portmask <0xXXXXXXXX-XXXXXXXX> on VLAN <id>

snTrapSTPBPDUGuardExpire.name: snTrapSTPBPDUGuardExpire
snTrapSTPBPDUGuardExpire.description: The SNMP notification that is generated when a port is re-enabled after being disabled due to BPDU Guard Violation. Format: STP: BPDU Guard re-enabled on VLAN <id> port <slot>/<port>

snTrapPortLoopDetection.name: snTrapPortLoopDetection
snTrapPortLoopDetection.description: The SNMP notification is generated when a port loop is detected. Format: LOOP DETECTION: VLAN <id>, port <slot>/<port> detect, putting into err-disable state

snTrapNoFreeTcamEntry.name: snTrapNoFreeTcamEntry
snTrapNoFreeTcamEntry.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when system is running out of TCAM spaces allocated for routing entries.

snTrapStackingMasterElected.name: snTrapStackingMasterElected
snTrapStackingMasterElected.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a unit is elected as Master unit for the stacking system.

snTrapStackingUnitAdded.name: snTrapStackingUnitAdded
snTrapStackingUnitAdded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a unit has been added to the stacking system.

snTrapStackingUnitDeleted.name: snTrapStackingUnitDeleted
snTrapStackingUnitDeleted.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a unit has been deleted from the stacking system.

snTrapStackingChasPwrSupplyOK.name: snTrapStackingChasPwrSupplyOK
snTrapStackingChasPwrSupplyOK.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a power supply operational status changed from failure to normal for a stacking system.

snTrapStackingChasPwrSupplyFailed.name: snTrapStackingChasPwrSupplyFailed
snTrapStackingChasPwrSupplyFailed.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a power supply operational status changed from normal to failure for a stacking system.

snTrapStackingChasFanNormal.name: snTrapStackingChasFanNormal
snTrapStackingChasFanNormal.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a fan operational status changed from failure to normal for a stacking system

snTrapStackingChasFanFailed.name: snTrapStackingChasFanFailed
snTrapStackingChasFanFailed.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a fan fails to operate normally for a stacking system.

snTrapStackingManagementMACChanged.name: snTrapStackingManagementMACChanged
snTrapStackingManagementMACChanged.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the managemnet MAC address of a stacking system has been changed.

snTrapStackingTemperatureWarning.name: snTrapStackingTemperatureWarning
snTrapStackingTemperatureWarning.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the actual temperature reading is above the warning temperature threshold for a stack sytem.

snTrapIfIndexAssignmentChanged.name: snTrapIfIndexAssignmentChanged
snTrapIfIndexAssignmentChanged.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the Interface Index (IfIndex) assignment for the physical interfaces was changed.

snTrapPBRConfigChanged.name: snTrapPBRConfigChanged
snTrapPBRConfigChanged.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a Policy Based Routing (PBR) routemap is bound or unbound either globally or to an interface.

snTrapChasPwrSupplyRPSAdd.name: snTrapChasPwrSupplyRPSAdd
snTrapChasPwrSupplyRPSAdd.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an External Redundant Power Supply (RPS2-EIF) is added to the system.

snTrapChasPwrSupplyRPSRemove.name: snTrapChasPwrSupplyRPSRemove
snTrapChasPwrSupplyRPSRemove.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an External Redundant Power Supply (RPS2-EIF) is removed from the system.

snTrapModuleStatusChange.name: snTrapModuleStatusChange
snTrapModuleStatusChange.description: The SNMP notification that is generated when a module's operational state changes. The management entity receiving the notification can identify the module and the event by referencing snChasUnitIndex, snAgentBrdIndex, snAgentBrdModuleStatus. In case of a module-down event, the varbind snAgGblTrapMessage is a text string that describes the cause. In case of module-up event, snAgGblTrapMessage is a null string.

snTrapChasHighSpeedFansNeeded.name: snTrapChasHighSpeedFansNeeded
snTrapChasHighSpeedFansNeeded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when chassis doesn't have high speed fans for specific modules

snTrapSysmaxReverted.name: snTrapSysmaxReverted
snTrapSysmaxReverted.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the revertible sysmax elements are reverted during the card bringup if they can not be accomodated in the available memory.

snTrapSysmaxLeftLowMem.name: snTrapSysmaxLeftLowMem
snTrapSysmaxLeftLowMem.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when its found during bootup that the configured sysmax set shall leave less than 10% available memory free.

snTrapSysMemoryLowThreshold.name: snTrapSysMemoryLowThreshold
snTrapSysMemoryLowThreshold.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the available dynamic memory in a card is below 5% of the installed physical memory.

snTrapSysMemoryOutThreshold.name: snTrapSysMemoryOutThreshold
snTrapSysMemoryOutThreshold.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the dynamic memory fails to be allocated in a system.

snTrapLinkOAMLinkDown.name: snTrapLinkOAMLinkDown
snTrapLinkOAMLinkDown.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when Link-OAM port link status has changed to down.

snTrapLinkOAMLinkUp.name: snTrapLinkOAMLinkUp
snTrapLinkOAMLinkUp.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when Link-OAM port link status has changed to up.

snTrapI2CAccessLog.name: snTrapI2CAccessLog
snTrapI2CAccessLog.description: The SNMP trap that is generated to provide information about state of the management module's I2C accesses.

snTrapLinkOAMLoopbackEntered.name: snTrapLinkOAMLoopbackEntered
snTrapLinkOAMLoopbackEntered.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when Link-OAM port has entered loopback mode. The link is not useful for data transfer any more.

snTrapLinkOAMLoopbackCleared.name: snTrapLinkOAMLoopbackCleared
snTrapLinkOAMLoopbackCleared.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when Link-OAM port has entered loopback mode. The link is not useful for data transfer any more.

snTrapLicenseAdded.name: snTrapLicenseAdded
snTrapLicenseAdded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a new license is added to the system.

snTrapLicenseRemoved.name: snTrapLicenseRemoved
snTrapLicenseRemoved.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an existing license is removed from the system.

snTrapLicenseExpires.name: snTrapLicenseExpires
snTrapLicenseExpires.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a trial license is about to expire. This trap is generated daily for last 3 days and every 2 hours on the last day of expire.

snTrapLicenseExpired.name: snTrapLicenseExpired
snTrapLicenseExpired.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a trial license has expired.

snTrapUDLDCrcFailureDetected.name: snTrapUDLDCrcFailureDetected
snTrapUDLDCrcFailureDetected.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when UDLD detects CRC failures on PDUs received on a port

snTrapDot1agCfmRemoteMEPAgeOut.name: snTrapDot1agCfmRemoteMEPAgeOut
snTrapDot1agCfmRemoteMEPAgeOut.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when 802.1ag Remote MEP ages out.

snTrapDot1agCfmRemoteMEPUp.name: snTrapDot1agCfmRemoteMEPUp
snTrapDot1agCfmRemoteMEPUp.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when 802.1ag Remote MEP is up.

snTrapDot1agCfmDomainCrossConnection.name: snTrapDot1agCfmDomainCrossConnection
snTrapDot1agCfmDomainCrossConnection.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when 802.1ag domain gets cross-connected.

snTrapDot1agCfmDuplicateMEPId.name: snTrapDot1agCfmDuplicateMEPId
snTrapDot1agCfmDuplicateMEPId.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when 802.1ag Remote MEP reports a duplicate MEP Id that conflicts with local MEP Id.

snTrapStackingStandbyElected.name: snTrapStackingStandbyElected
snTrapStackingStandbyElected.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a unit is elected as Standby unit for the stacking system.

snTrapMacMoveThresholdRate.name: snTrapMacMoveThresholdRate
snTrapMacMoveThresholdRate.description: The SNMP notification is generated when MAC movement exceeding the certain threshold for a sampling interval is detected. Format: Mac-Move threshold-rate: MAC address <mac> moved from interface <port-id> to interface <port-id> for vlan <vlan-id>, <move-count> times exceeding the threshold rate <threshold-rate> for a sampling interval <interval> seconds

snTrapMacMoveIntervalHistory.name: snTrapMacMoveIntervalHistory
snTrapMacMoveIntervalHistory.description: The SNMP notification is generated every user configured interval, summarizing the moves in the interval . Format: Mac-Move Interval-History: <#macs> macs moved in last <interval> seconds. Total number of mac moves in the interval is <#moves>

snTrapStackingMixedModeChanged.name: snTrapStackingMixedModeChanged
snTrapStackingMixedModeChanged.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a stacking system mode is changed. Format: The stacking system is changed to Mixed Stacking mode

snTrapSysMonErrorDetect.name: snTrapSysMonErrorDetect
snTrapSysMonErrorDetect.description: The SNMP notification is generated when SYSMON detects internal error.

snTrapMacNotification.name: snTrapMacNotification
snTrapMacNotification.description: The SNMP notification is generated when MAC event(s) is(are) detected. Format: MAC-Event:MAC:<mac>-VLAN:<vlan-id>-PORT:<port-id>-ACT:<action>::MAC:<mac>-VLAN:<vlan-id>-PORT:<port-id>-ACT:<action>:: ... ...MAC:<mac>-VLAN:<vlan-id>-PORT:<port-id>-ACT:<action>:: where action: 1-MAC addition; 2-MAC deletion; 3-remove all MACs; 4-remove MAC from a port; 5-remove MAC from a VLAN; 6-remove MAC from a VLAN on a port

snTrapMacEventBufferFull.name: snTrapMacEventBufferFull
snTrapMacEventBufferFull.description: The SNMP notification is generated when MAC event buffer full is detected. Format: MAC-Event: The Buffer is full, FDB table walk is required

snTrapStpDesignatedGuardDetect.name: snTrapStpDesignatedGuardDetect
snTrapStpDesignatedGuardDetect.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when VLAN's ports's Designated-Guard detect.

snTrapStpDesignatedGuardDisable.name: snTrapStpDesignatedGuardDisable
snTrapStpDesignatedGuardDisable.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when VLAN's ports's Designated-Guard disable.

snTrapLicenseNNLLTrialNotify.name: snTrapLicenseNNLLTrialNotify
snTrapLicenseNNLLTrialNotify.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a non-node locked licensed feature is enabled with no a non-node locked license installed. Format: Stack <stack_id>: Use of the <feature_name> feature requires a license to be purchased and installed within <day> days.

snTrapLicenseNNLLTrialExpiry.name: snTrapLicenseNNLLTrialExpiry
snTrapLicenseNNLLTrialExpiry.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a non-node locked licensed feature is enabled after 30-44 days with no a non-node locked license installed. This message will be displayed 3 times day 30, day 37, day 44. Format: Stack <stack_id>: The <feature_name> feature has been activated for <day> days. To ensure compliance, please purchase and install a license as soon as possible

snTrapLicenseNNLLNonCompliant.name: snTrapLicenseNNLLNonCompliant
snTrapLicenseNNLLNonCompliant.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a non-node locked licensed feature is enabled after 45+ days whit no a non-node locked license installed. Or deletion of an installed license if any of the associated features are still enabled. This message will be displayed daily. Format: Stack <stack_id>: THIS UNIT IS NOT COMPLIANT. A license for <feature_name> feature must be purchased and installed or the feature <feature_name> must be deactivated to become compliant with the terms and conditions of use

snTrapLicenseNNLLDelete.name: snTrapLicenseNNLLDelete
snTrapLicenseNNLLDelete.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a non-node locked licensed feature is enabled after a non-node locked license is deleted. Format: Stack <stack_id>: The <license_name> license has been deleted on this unit and is available for redeployment on another unit in accordance with the terms and conditions of use. All features associated to this license must be disabled

snTrapStackingShowStackConnect.name: snTrapStackingShowStackConnect
snTrapStackingShowStackConnect.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the background diagnosis detects the connection errors to notify the user to check the connections in a stacking system Format: Background diagnosis detects connection errors. Please use show stack conn to view detailed connections

snTrapChasFanOK.name: snTrapChasFanOK
snTrapChasFanOK.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a fan operational status changed from failure to normal or change in the fan speed due to temperature variations downwards.

snTrapTemperatureOK.name: snTrapTemperatureOK
snTrapTemperatureOK.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the actual temperature reading is below the warning temperature threshold.

snTrapCAMOverflow.name: snTrapCAMOverflow
snTrapCAMOverflow.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when any CAM partition becomes full.

snTrapOpticalMonitoringWarning.name: snTrapOpticalMonitoringWarning
snTrapOpticalMonitoringWarning.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if there is a warning during optical monitoring. The first varbind, snAgGblTrapMessage, will have a detailed message on the cause of event. The second optional varbind, ifIndex, points to the affected interface originating this event. If an event does not have associated port, or has multiple associated ports, then ifIndex will have maximum value 0x7ffffff.

snTrapOpticalMonitoringAlarm.name: snTrapOpticalMonitoringAlarm
snTrapOpticalMonitoringAlarm.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if there is an alarm during optical monitoring. The first varbind, snAgGblTrapMessage, will have a detailed message on the cause of event. The second optional varbind, ifIndex, points to the affected interface originating this event. If an event does not have associated port, or has multiple associated ports, then ifIndex will have maximum value 0x7ffffff.

snTrapOpticalMonitoringError.name: snTrapOpticalMonitoringError
snTrapOpticalMonitoringError.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if there is an error during optical monitoring. The first varbind, snAgGblTrapMessage, will have a detailed message on the cause of event. The second optional varbind, ifIndex, points to the affected interface originating this event. If an event does not have associated port, or has multiple associated ports, then ifIndex will have maximum value 0x7ffffff.

snTrapPosMonitoringWarning.name: snTrapPosMonitoringWarning
snTrapPosMonitoringWarning.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if there is a warning during POS alarm monitoring. The first varbind, snAgGblTrapMessage, will have a detailed message on the cause of event. The second optional varbind, ifIndex, points to the affected interface originating this event. If an event does not have associated port, or has multiple associated ports, then ifIndex will have maximum value 0x7ffffff.

snTrapPosMonitoringAlarm.name: snTrapPosMonitoringAlarm
snTrapPosMonitoringAlarm.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if there is an alarm up/down during POS alarm monitoring. The first varbind, snAgGblTrapMessage, will have a detailed message on the cause of event. The second optional varbind, ifIndex, points to the affected interface originating this event. If an event does not have associated port, or has multiple associated ports, then ifIndex will have maximum value 0x7ffffff.

snTrapPosMonitoringError.name: snTrapPosMonitoringError
snTrapPosMonitoringError.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if there is an error during POS alarm monitoring. The first varbind, snAgGblTrapMessage, will have a detailed message on the cause of event. The second optional varbind, ifIndex, points to the affected interface originating this event. If an event does not have associated port, or has multiple associated ports, then ifIndex will have maximum value 0x7ffffff.

snTrapXfpSfpIncompatibleOptics.name: snTrapXfpSfpIncompatibleOptics
snTrapXfpSfpIncompatibleOptics.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if optics is incompatible with port configuration.

snTrapTMLoggingStart.name: snTrapTMLoggingStart
snTrapTMLoggingStart.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if TM logging is started by an event trigger.

snTrapTMLoggingStop.name: snTrapTMLoggingStop
snTrapTMLoggingStop.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if TM logging stopped due to storage full.

snTrapTMLoggingRestart.name: snTrapTMLoggingRestart
snTrapTMLoggingRestart.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if TM logging restarted after user clearing the log.

snTrapXfpSfpNotFoundryOptics.name: snTrapXfpSfpNotFoundryOptics
snTrapXfpSfpNotFoundryOptics.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if optics vendor is not Foundry Networks.

snTrapTMRecoverySlotReset.name: snTrapTMRecoverySlotReset
snTrapTMRecoverySlotReset.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when TM recovery slot reset is triggered.

snTrapTMEgressDataError.name: snTrapTMEgressDataError
snTrapTMEgressDataError.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when system detects egress data errors on Traffic Manager. For e.g. Fabric Monitoring : TM Egress data errors detected on LP <num>/TM <num>

snTrapSFMLoggingRestart.name: snTrapSFMLoggingRestart
snTrapSFMLoggingRestart.description: The SNMP trap that is generated if SFM logging restarted after user clearing the log.

snTrapNotEnoughFapLinks.name: snTrapNotEnoughFapLinks
snTrapNotEnoughFapLinks.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when LP FAP (Fabric Adapter Processor) has not enough links to maintain the line rate.

snTrapSFMLinkDown.name: snTrapSFMLinkDown
snTrapSFMLinkDown.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a link from LP Traffic Manager to SFM Fabric Element is down. For eg. Fabric Monitoring Link Down : SFM <num>/FE <num>/Link <num>, LP <num>/TM <num>

snTrapSFMLinkUp.name: snTrapSFMLinkUp
snTrapSFMLinkUp.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a link from LP Traffic Manager to SFM Fabric Element is up. For eg. Fabric Monitoring Link Up : SFM <num>/FE <num>/Link <num>, LP <num>/TM <num>

snTrapSFMAccessError.name: snTrapSFMAccessError
snTrapSFMAccessError.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when system fails to access a SFM Fabric Element. For e.g. Fabric Monitoring : Device access failure in SFM <num>/FE <num>

snTrapSFMStatusChange.name: snTrapSFMStatusChange
snTrapSFMStatusChange.description: The SNMP notification that is generated when there is a change in the operational state of the Switch Fabric Module (SFM). For example, System: Health Monitoring: SFM <num> powered off due to failure detection

snTrapLPFabricStatusChange.name: snTrapLPFabricStatusChange
snTrapLPFabricStatusChange.description: Health Monitoring: LP Fabric status change.

snTrapModuleNPLockupIndication.name: snTrapModuleNPLockupIndication
snTrapModuleNPLockupIndication.description: The SNMP notification that is generated for the module's NP health monitoring to indicate that a lockup and recovery have occurred. Expressed in number of times in the past 1 hour

snTrapModuleNPLockupThresholdExceeded.name: snTrapModuleNPLockupThresholdExceeded
snTrapModuleNPLockupThresholdExceeded.description: The SNMP notification that is generated for the module's NP health monitoring when the threshold for lockup and recovery of any NP within the module have been reached. The threshold value is 5 times in the past 1 hour.

snTrapSFMAutoTuneStart.name: snTrapSFMAutoTuneStart
snTrapSFMAutoTuneStart.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when Auto tuning starts on the fabric side

snTrapSFMAutoTuneFails.name: snTrapSFMAutoTuneFails
snTrapSFMAutoTuneFails.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when Auto tuning fails on the fabric side

snTrapSFMAutoTuneComplete.name: snTrapSFMAutoTuneComplete
snTrapSFMAutoTuneComplete.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when Auto tuning completes on the fabric side

snTrapTMAutoTuneStart.name: snTrapTMAutoTuneStart
snTrapTMAutoTuneStart.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when Auto tuning starts on the TM side

snTrapTMAutoTuneFails.name: snTrapTMAutoTuneFails
snTrapTMAutoTuneFails.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when Auto tuning fails on the TM side

snTrapTMAutoTuneComplete.name: snTrapTMAutoTuneComplete
snTrapTMAutoTuneComplete.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when Auto tuning completes on the TM side

snTrapNPILKNCRCError.name: snTrapNPILKNCRCError
snTrapNPILKNCRCError.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when packet drops are observed in 2x100G ports because of Interlaken CRC errors

snTrapARPMACMovement.name: snTrapARPMACMovement
snTrapARPMACMovement.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the MAC address associated with a host IP is changed.

snTrapChassisFanSpeedLow.name: snTrapChassisFanSpeedLow
snTrapChassisFanSpeedLow.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when all chassis fans change to low speed.

snTrapChassisFanSpeedMedium.name: snTrapChassisFanSpeedMedium
snTrapChassisFanSpeedMedium.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when all chassis fans change to medium speed.

snTrapChassisFanSpeedMedHigh.name: snTrapChassisFanSpeedMedHigh
snTrapChassisFanSpeedMedHigh.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when all chassis fans change to medium high speed.

snTrapChassisFanSpeedHigh.name: snTrapChassisFanSpeedHigh
snTrapChassisFanSpeedHigh.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when all chassis fans change to high speed.

snTrapFIPSModeEnable.name: snTrapFIPSModeEnable
snTrapFIPSModeEnable.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when FIPS mode is enabled.

snTrapFIPSModeDisable.name: snTrapFIPSModeDisable
snTrapFIPSModeDisable.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when FIPS mode is disabled.

snTrapFIPSHostZeroized.name: snTrapFIPSHostZeroized
snTrapFIPSHostZeroized.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when host keys are zeroized in FIPS mode

snTrapFIPSSharedSecretZeroized.name: snTrapFIPSSharedSecretZeroized
snTrapFIPSSharedSecretZeroized.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when shared secret are zeroized in FIPS mode

snTrapFIPSPOSTStatus.name: snTrapFIPSPOSTStatus
snTrapFIPSPOSTStatus.description: The SNMP trap that is generated after POST.

snTrapFIPSCryptoModuleFailure.name: snTrapFIPSCryptoModuleFailure
snTrapFIPSCryptoModuleFailure.description: The SNMP trap that is generated on cryptographic module failure.

snTrapLicense2PortNotSupported.name: snTrapLicense2PortNotSupported
snTrapLicense2PortNotSupported.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a 2 port license cannot be applied due to hardware limitation.

snTrapOpticalMonitoringOK.name: snTrapOpticalMonitoringOK
snTrapOpticalMonitoringOK.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an interface transitions from an error to normal state because the alarms/warnings are below the threshold. snTrapOpticalMonitoringError would have been earlier generated when the interface transitioned to the error state. The first varbind, snAgGblTrapMessage, will have a detailed message on the cause of event. The second varbind, ifIndex, points to the affected interface originating this event. If an event does not have associated port, or has multiple associated ports, then ifIndex will have maximum value 0x7ffffff.

snTrapSFMAccessOK.name: snTrapSFMAccessOK
snTrapSFMAccessOK.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when system can successfully access an SFM Fabric Element. snTrapSFMAccessError would have been generated when the system failed to access the FE. For e.g. Fabric Monitoring : Device SFM <num>/FE <num> is OK to access.

snTrapUpgradeSingleCmdStart.name: snTrapUpgradeSingleCmdStart
snTrapUpgradeSingleCmdStart.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the single-command package upgrade has started. This happens after a successful download and validation of manifest file and before the first image download takes place.

snTrapUpgradeSingleCmdDone.name: snTrapUpgradeSingleCmdDone
snTrapUpgradeSingleCmdDone.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the single-command package upgrade completed, or partially completed. The table brcdSwPackageLoadResultTable lists the result of the upgrade.

snTrapAutoUpgradeStart.name: snTrapAutoUpgradeStart
snTrapAutoUpgradeStart.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an auto-upgrade on a line card has started.

snTrapAutoUpgradeDone.name: snTrapAutoUpgradeDone
snTrapAutoUpgradeDone.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the auto-upgrade of interface module completed.

snTrapTcamParityError.name: snTrapTcamParityError
snTrapTcamParityError.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the TCAM parity errors are detected on LP.

snTrapLPResetOnTcamError.name: snTrapLPResetOnTcamError
snTrapLPResetOnTcamError.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the LP reset due to TCAM parity errors crossing the threshold or TCAM integrity check failure.

snTrapSTPRootGuardViolation.name: snTrapSTPRootGuardViolation
snTrapSTPRootGuardViolation.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when STP Root Guard Violation occurs on a port. Format: STP: Root-protect port <slot>/<port>, VLAN <id> inconsistent (Received superior BPDU)

snTrapRSTPRootGuardViolation.name: snTrapRSTPRootGuardViolation
snTrapRSTPRootGuardViolation.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when STP Root Guard Violation occurs on a port. Format: RSTP: Root-protect port <slot>/<port>, VLAN <id> inconsistent (Received superior BPDU)
